bio.experienceSummary: I have an extensive background in childcare and have worked with both large groups of children as well as individuals for the past 8 years. I have experience in teaching children ages 4-7 and am educated in aspects of child development. I have an expertise in caring for toddlers and adolescents, but I am also able to care for infants. I'm a highly organized, high-spirited, and creative person, and absolutely adore spending time with children.

I hold a Bachelor of Fine Arts in Acting with a minor in Dance and am a certified Registered Behavioral Therapist (RBT) with specialized training in Applied Behavior Analysis (ABA). I have extensive experience working with children from infancy through their teenage years, including those with high-support Autism. My approach is energetic, creative, and child-centered, incorporating engaging activities such as games, crafts, and music to foster both learning and enjoyment. I have experience managing large groups of children and prioritizing positive reinforcement to ensure a fun and supportive environment. I am passionate about nurturing self-love and confidence in every child, respecting their individuality, and empowering them to thrive.

Hi! My name is Ashley and I'm a fun and creative sitter. I've worked as a camp counselor throughout junior high and high school as well as babysat for friends and family. During my first two years in college, I worked as a tutor and mentor for middle school students, and I currently work as an after school teacher at a daycare in Atlanta. I am very creative, with ample experience in creating educational activities under science, technology, engineering, arts, and mathematics (S. T. E. A. M). I am vaccinated from COVID-19, and I take very possible precaution. I am tested weekly, and always wear a double mask and sanitize my hands and belongings. I can't wait to work with you and your family!

I'm a passionate childcare provider with six years of experience caring for children of all ages. I believe that every child deserves a safe and nurturing environment in which to grow and develop, and I strive to provide that for each child in my care.

I'm known for my patience, creativity, and friendly nature. I enjoy playing outdoor sports and physical games, as well as board games and puzzles with children. I also prioritize keeping the parents informed about their child's day and any issues that arise, adapting to their preferred communication method.

In terms of household rules, I'm very comfortable enforcing them and fostering a structured environment. I have completed First Aid Training, and I'm willing to help with cooking, meal preparation, carpooling, light housekeeping, and travel. I'm confident that I have the skills and experience to provide your family with the high-quality childcare you're seeking.

description.originalText: AlaZia is Amazing all around I 100% recommend her as you’re caregiver

bio.experienceSummary:
As a childcare provider with over 20 years of experience, I'm dedicated to fostering the growth and development of children. My passion lies in making a positive impact on their lives while providing reliable support to families. My patient and calm nature, coupled with my creativity and friendly approach, allows me to connect with children and create a nurturing environment. I believe in open communication with parents, providing regular updates and following their preferred communication method. Regarding household rules, I adhere to the parents' guidelines to ensure consistency for the children.

From outdoor sports to educational games, I enjoy a variety of activities that promote physical, mental, and emotional well-being. With a background in Early Childhood Education and coursework in Early Child Development, I'm equipped with the knowledge and skills to nurture children's holistic growth.

description.displayText: This was the first time we ever had a sitter and Charisma was amazing! She is such a nice and warm person, and I felt completely at ease leaving my son with her!

bio.experienceSummary: Hi! I am a 27-year-old occupational therapist. I recently graduated with my Doctorate in Occupational Therapy. Since high school, I have been babysitting children of all ages. From my experiences working at a sleep away camp, a school for individuals with cerebral palsy, and an after school swim group, I know how to make an enjoyable and safe time with the kids I babysit. I have experience with children with different disabilities too.

Hello! I am a college and career adviser at a Highschool and have graduated with a bachelors in psychology. I'll be getting my masters in social work and have worked with children my entire life. I have been a full time nanny for most of my college career, and am now looking for part time work to supplement working in education! I love children, and know that I want to work with them for the rest of my life.

description.displayText: LOVE Stella. We hired her as our nanny and my girls absolutely adore her. She's smart, kind, caring and thoughtful. We hope she is able to stay with us until my kids are all in school! :)
description.originalText: LOVE Stella. We hired her as our nanny and my girls absolutely adore her. She's smart, kind, caring and thoughtful. We hope she is able to stay with us until my kids are all in school! :)

bio.experienceSummary:
I'd describe my personality as fun, attentive, and caring.

I like working with kids because I grew up in a pretty large family and love being a part of the development and growth of children! I love seeing the moment a new skill or trait clicks for them, and I love helping them turn into the people they were created to be!

I started working with kids in middle school through babysitting and working in the church nursery and kids classes. I worked as a full time nanny for a few months after graduating college. I've been babysitting and nannying off and on since then, and most recently worked as an afterschool program coordinator with elementary and middle school students.

In my spare time, I like to read lots of fun books, watch movies, and go for walks! I also love music and love to attend concerts in the Atlanta area!

description.originalText: Katherine was so wonderful with our 4 year old. Our daughter even asked us the next day when she would be coming back! Definitely recommend Katherine!

bio.experienceSummary: Hi there! My name is Nia and I'm 23-year-old from central Maine who is now living in Atlanta. I attend Emory University where I am receiving my Masters of Public Health. Over the past three years I have nannied for a family in Boston during my undergraduate studies and took care of their 7-year-old son. I would feel comfortable tutoring kids in any subjects they might need help with. I also played division one college basketball and love being active! Some of my favorite hobbies are hiking, swimming, and window-shopping! I have grown up with 2 dogs, so I am very comfortable with pets as well. I am fully vaccinated against COVID-19 and can provide proof!

Hi, there! My name is Destiny, but I prefer Dessy, and I am a 19-year-old full time nanny in the greater Atlanta area. I'm in school pursuing my bachelors degree in CRJU, hoping to get my law degree within the next four years. My school is fully online, meaning I have a flexible schedule for work! I love animals, myself having rescued 3 cats and a guinea pig, lol! I love cooking, exploring, learning about new things, and creating memories! 

I'd describe my personality as broad-minded, energetic, and adaptable 

I like working with kids because it's fun to do. You take these little human beings, and everything you say or do to them shapes who they'll be as they grow. Adults are supposed to be their biggest supporters, their best teachers, and someone they can trust. We make their childhood, and I personally want them to look back when they're 30 and have their own kids and remember something I said to or did for them that impacted them in a good way.
